The Edo State Governor, Mr Godwin Obaseki, has approved the immediate promotion of all civil and public servants whose promotions were due in 2022. In a statement, the Head of Service, Anthony Okungbowa, said the directive was in line with the government’s commitment to the prompt and regular promotion of civil/public servants. Okungbowa said, “No other state in Nigeria has approved promotions this year, not even the Federal Government. So, this is a major milestone and the governor deserves accolades for prioritising the welfare of workers.” He added that the development was in line with the new paradigm in the service which emphasises and prioritises the welfare of civil/public servants in Edo State and in particular, that civil and public servants are promoted as and when due. He added, “Ministries, Departments and Agencies are by this announcement directed to commence and conclude the process of the promotion of eligible officers without delay. All Accounting Officers are to ensure strict compliance with this directive.”